14/12/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- Greece's permanent representative to the UN, Ambassador Adamantios Vasilakis, is hinting that UN-sponsored bilateral negotiations with Skopje on Macedonia's constitutional name may succeed.
He expressed moderate optimism about a final settlement and said Greece has made every effort to ensure a mutually acceptable solution.
(Makfax - 14/12/04;
MPA - 13/12/04)
